    </template><strong>Note: </strong><strong>How the job calculates Pi:</s=
trong> The Spark job estimates a value of Pi using the <a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Monte_Carlo_method" target=3D"_blank">Monte Carlo meth=
od</a>. It generates x,y points on a coordinate plane that models a circle =
enclosed by a unit square. The input argument (1000) determines the number =
of x,y pairs to generate; the more pairs generated, the greater the accurac=
y of the estimation. This estimation leverages Managed Apache Spark worker =
nodes to parallelize the computation. For more information, see <a href=3D"=
https://academo.org/demos/estimating-pi-monte-carlo/" target=3D"_blank">Est=
imating Pi using the Monte Carlo Method</a> and see <a href=3D"https://gith=
ub.com/Apache/spark/blob/master/examples/src/main/java/org/apache/spark/exa=
mples/JavaSparkPi.java" target=3D"_blank">JavaSparkPi.java on GitHub</a>.
</ql-infobox>
